comments.body: Interesting!  By the way, I didn't disagree with your subspecies ID, just confirmed the part that I knew about.  So it's being ssp. borealis.

observation.description: Open subalpine outcrop/fellfield on the summit ridge of Circle Peak, calcareous bedrock (marble). S to SE aspect, elevation just under 6000 ft.
